docs.abstract: Anti-racism activists have detailed concerns that are not only about symbols or slurs but also about entire systems governing how Americans live.
docs.snippet: Anti-racism activists have detailed concerns that are not only about symbols or slurs but also about entire systems governing how Americans live.
docs.lead_paragraph: One recent afternoon, while washing his car, Greg Reese, a white stay-at-home dad in Campton, Ky., peeled off the Confederate flag magnet he had placed on its trunk six years earlier. He did not put it back on.

headline.main: White Americans Say They Are Waking Up to Racism. What Will It Add Up To?
headline.print_headline: White and Awakened to Racism,  And Wondering What to Do Next

docs.abstract: Many in Beijing believe that the United States will remain hostile to the country’s rise, regardless of who is president.

docs.lead_paragraph: All along China’s leaders publicly professed indifference to the American presidential election, having concluded that no matter who won, the United States would remain irreconcilably opposed to the country’s rise.

docs.abstract: More than 4,000 people were detained, but allies of the opposition leader Aleksei A. Navalny called Sunday's demonstrations a success.
docs.snippet: More than 4,000 people were detained, but allies of the opposition leader Aleksei A. Navalny called Sunday's demonstrations a success.
docs.lead_paragraph: Tens of thousands of people turned out across Russia on Sunday for a second consecutive weekend rally in support of a jailed opposition leader, Aleksei A. Navalny. But where the protesters went, so did the police, meeting them in sometimes brutal clashes.

headline.main: In Photos: Crowds of Police Couldn’t Quell Russia’s Pro-Navalny Protests

docs.abstract: The Turner Contemporary Gallery hosts an exhibit exploring the U.S. civil rights movement, as well as two installations from contemporary Black British artists who find inspiration in the local community.

docs.lead_paragraph: MARGATE, England — When the artists Kelly Abbott and Victoria Barrow Williams heard that the Turner Contemporary Gallery was hosting an exhibition focused on art associated with the civil rights movement in the American South, they felt confused.

docs.abstract: Recent protests that have stirred a reckoning on racism helped bring thousands out to celebrate a holiday commemorating the end of slavery in the United States.
docs.snippet: Recent protests that have stirred a reckoning on racism helped bring thousands out to celebrate a holiday commemorating the end of slavery in the United States.
docs.lead_paragraph: Thousands of people flooded New York City’s streets, parks and public plazas on Friday to celebrate Juneteenth, a holiday commemorating the end of slavery in the United States that until a recent wave of protests had not been widely recognized outside black communities.

headline.main: ‘Sad and Joyful’: N.Y.C. Marks Juneteenth After a Month of Protest
headline.print_headline: ‘Sad and Joyful at the Same Time’

docs.abstract: President Trump’s attempt to revive his re-election bid sputtered badly as he traveled to Tulsa for his first mass rally in months but found a small crowd and delivered a disjointed speech.
docs.snippet: President Trump’s attempt to revive his re-election bid sputtered badly as he traveled to Tulsa for his first mass rally in months but found a small crowd and delivered a disjointed speech.
docs.lead_paragraph: TULSA, Okla. — President Trump’s attempt to revive his re-election campaign sputtered badly on Saturday night as he traveled to Tulsa for his first mass rally in months and found a far smaller crowd than his aides had promised him, then delivered a disjointed speech that did not address the multiple crises facing the nation or scandals battering him in Washington.

headline.main: Trump Rally Fizzles as Attendance Falls Short of Campaign’s Expectations
headline.print_headline: Trump’s Plan For a Big Rally Sputters Badly

docs.abstract: Claims about the involvement of anti-fascist activists in protests of racism show the many ways false information spreads inside communities online.
docs.snippet: Claims about the involvement of anti-fascist activists in protests of racism show the many ways false information spreads inside communities online.
docs.lead_paragraph: In recent weeks, as demonstrations against racism spread across the country, residents in at least 41 U.S. cities and towns became alarmed by rumors that the loose collective of anti-fascist activists known as antifa was headed to their area, according to an analysis by The New York Times. In many cases, they contacted their local law enforcement for help.

headline.main: 41 Cities, Many Sources: How False Antifa Rumors Spread Locally
headline.print_headline: Brewing Rumors Of Antifa At Home
